# Overview

💡 MY IDEA: AI-ASSISTED INTERVIEW SYSTEM (HR-CONTROLLED)
📌 Core Idea
My idea is to build an AI-assisted interview system where HR stays fully in control, and AI is used only as a support tool, not as a decision-maker.
The system helps companies save time, standardize evaluations, and conduct scalable interviews, while keeping human judgment at the center.
🎯 Problem I Am Solving
Today, companies face these problems:
Too many resumes to review manually
Inconsistent resume evaluation
Limited interviewer availability
High interview scheduling overhead
Biased or unstructured interview feedback
At the same time:
Fully automated AI hiring systems are risky
HR teams don’t trust black-box decisions
✅ My Solution
I propose a step-by-step AI interview workflow where:
HR filters resumes manually
AI evaluates resumes and interviews
HR makes all final decisions
AI never rejects or selects candidates on its own.
🧠 How the System Works (High Level)
Resumes are already available in the system.
HR shortlists resumes manually using simple rules.
AI scores shortlisted resumes using Google Gemini (score + missing skills).
HR reviews scores and selects candidates.
Selected candidates receive a selection confirmation email.
HR team contacts selected candidates for next steps.
🔑 Key Design Principles
HR-first approach
AI as an assistant, not a judge
Explainable scores and reports
No automatic rejection
Clear separation of responsibilities
🧱 Technology Stack Used
Frontend: React + TypeScript
Backend: Python + FastAPI
Database & Auth: Supabase
Resume AI: Google Gemini API
Email: Resend API
🚀 Why This Idea Is Strong
✔ Practical and realistic
✔ Easy to explain to HR teams
✔ Scales from local setup to production
✔ Avoids legal and ethical risks
✔ Suitable for a final-year engineering project
✔ Can be extended into a real startup product
🏁 One-Line Summary (Your Signature Line)
An AI-assisted interview system where HR controls the hiring process, AI evaluates skills, and decisions always remain human.